# LiveArch hosted server — environment variables (all optional).
#
# No env vars? The server runs with the filesystem backend under server/.data/ —
# perfect for `next dev` and small self-hosting.

# --- Postgres (Neon) ---------------------------------------------------------
# Set DATABASE_URL to switch storage from the filesystem to Postgres. Provision
# Neon via the Vercel Marketplace (`vercel integration add neon`) and it injects
# this automatically; or paste a Neon/Postgres connection string here.
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@host/db?sslmode=require

# --- Billing (optional) ------------------------------------------------------
# Unset (default): `livearch upgrade` changes the plan immediately (no payment).
# Set to 'stripe' to route upgrades through Stripe Checkout instead: the CLI
# opens a hosted payment page and the plan is applied by the webhook below.
# LIVEARCH_BILLING=stripe
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...              # from `stripe listen` or the dashboard
# STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=price_...                   # a monthly Price id for the Pro plan
# STRIPE_PRICE_TEAM=price_...                  # a monthly Price id for the Team plan
# Webhook endpoint to configure in Stripe:  <origin>/api/billing/webhook
# Also run: cd server && npm install stripe

# --- Sign in with GitHub (optional) -----------------------------------------
# Register an OAuth app at https://github.com/settings/developers with callback
# <origin>/api/auth/github/callback, then set these to enable /api/auth/github.
# GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
# GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
